sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as React Frontend<br/>(mcpClient.js)
    participant NGX as Nginx<br/>(port 80)
    participant MCP as FastMCP Server<br/>(mcp_server.py)

    Note over FE,MCP: Phase 1 — Initialization Handshake

    FE->>NGX: POST /mcp {jsonrpc:2.0, method:initialize, id:1}
    NGX->>MCP: forward to backend:8000/mcp
    MCP-->>FE: 200 OK + mcp-session-id: abc123<br/>SSE stream opens (Content-Type: text/event-stream)

    FE->>MCP: POST /mcp {method:notifications/initialized}
    MCP-->>FE: 204 No Content

    Note over FE,MCP: Phase 2 — Tool Discovery

    FE->>MCP: POST /mcp {method:tools/list, id:2}
    MCP-->>FE: SSE: {result:{tools:[...40+ tool schemas with names/params/descriptions]}}

    Note over FE,MCP: Phase 3 — Tool Call with Streaming Response

    FE->>MCP: POST /mcp {method:tools/call, id:3,<br/>params:{name:full_aws_scan, arguments:{aws_access_key_id:..., region:us-east-1}}}

    Note over MCP: Execute tool:<br/>boto3 calls + security analysis + LLM summary

    MCP-->>FE: SSE: data: {jsonrpc:2.0, result:{content:[{type:text, text:...}]}}
    MCP-->>FE: SSE: data: [DONE]

    Note over FE,MCP: Phase 4 — stdio Transport (Claude Desktop)

    Note over FE,MCP: Claude Desktop spawns FastMCP as subprocess<br/>stdin: raw JSON-RPC messages<br/>stdout: raw JSON-RPC responses<br/>No HTTP, no Nginx — direct process I/O<br/>Credentials via env vars in claude_desktop_config_example.json
